SYNOPSIS (OPTIONAL)
===================
   string db_error(intÂ handle)

DESCRIPTION
===========
Return a string describing the error which occured during the last database
transaction. If the last database transaction was successful, this call
returns 0.

The function is available only if the driver is compiled with mySQL support.
In that case, __MYSQL__ is defined.

The efun triggers a privilege violation ("mysql", "db_error").

Added in 3.2.9 . LDMud 3.2.11 added the privilege violation.

   See Also:
      db_affected_rows(E), db_conv_string(E),
      db_close(E),db_coldefs(E),db_connect(E), db_exec(E), db_fetch(E),
      db_handles(E),db_insert_id(E),*mysql*, privilege_violation(M)
